						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga III. Year 25: A.D. 1203.</hi> </p>						

						<p>Much damaged. Seems to record a grant of land as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā dēvadāṉam</hi> to the temple of Mayindīchiram Uḍaiyār by a native of Āriyambākkam. The inscription further states that the individual shall measure out paddy at the rate of 60 <hi rend="italic">kaṇḍakams</hi> on the produce of a <hi rend="italic">kār</hi> crop, and 10 <hi rend="italic">kaṇḍakams</hi> on a <hi rend="italic">picānam</hi> crop.</p>						

						</summary>
